<DOC><DOCNO> AP900416-0224 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-16-90 1428EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r s BC-SportsPaper     04-16 0150</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Sports Paper,0155</SECOND><NOTE>Eds: Also running on business wire; no other versions planned.</NOTE><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The National, the sports daily that has beenpublishing editions in New York, Chicago and Los Angeles for 2{months, plans to begin editions this summer in San Diego and SanFrancisco.   Publisher Peter Price said Monday that he expects the San Diegoedition to start by July 1. The San Francisco edition will belaunched in July.   Price said the newspaper plans to add at least one city a monthduring the last five months of the year, but he didn't name thecities.   The National is currently distributing an average of about350,000 newspapers a day, and selling more than 200,000 copies aday, Price said.   He said the paper hopes to have editions in 10 to 12 cities bythe end of the year with average circulation ``approaching400,000.''</TEXT></DOC>